briefdescription.para: Information about a file, usually thought of as a binary byte stream stored on disk. A FileType can also represent a "virtual" file, such as an XML module in a larger XML document. Such a virtual file could theoretically be stored as a byte stream, as an independant file on disk or as a database record or set of records, even if this byte stream is never actually persisted as an independant disk file.
